HEADWORD: Portamento
<hw>Por`ta*men"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., fr.
<ets>portare</ets> to carry.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>In singing,
or in the use of the bow, a gradual carrying or lifting of the voice or
sound very smoothly from one note to another; a gliding from tone to
tone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portance</ent>⟦br⟧
